Package com.googlecode.cqengine

Interface Summary
IndexedCollection<O> A Java collection which can maintain indexes on the objects it contains, allowing objects matching complex queries to be retrieved with very low latency.
 

Class Summary
ConcurrentIndexedCollection<O> An implementation of Set and QueryEngine, thus providing ConcurrentIndexedCollection.retrieve(com.googlecode.cqengine.query.Query) methods for performing queries on the collection to retrieve matching objects, and ConcurrentIndexedCollection.addIndex(com.googlecode.cqengine.index.Index) methods allowing indexes to be added to the collection to improve query performance.
ObjectLockingIndexedCollection<O> Extends ConcurrentIndexedCollection with some specialized locking for applications in which multiple threads might try to add or remove the same object to/from an indexed collection concurrently.
TransactionalIndexedCollection<O> Extends ConcurrentIndexedCollection with support for READ_COMMITTED transaction isolation using Multiversion concurrency control (MVCC).
